.* Help for parameter FNAM
:HELP NAME='FNAM'.File Name (FNAM) - Help
:XH3.File Name (FNAM)
:P.
Specify the name of the file to analyze. This can be a specific file
name, a generic or all files in the specified library.
:P.
The possible values for File Name are:
:P.
:PARML.
:PT.Name
:PD.
Specify the file name to be analyzed.
:PT.Generic*
:PD.
Specify a generic file name where * is a wildcard. As an example, to
analyze files PAYROLL, PAYPROD and PAYTMP specify PAY*.
:EPARML.
:EHELP.
.* Help for parameter FLIB
:HELP NAME='FLIB'.File Name (FLIB) - Help
:XH3.File Library (FLIB)
:P.
Specify the library containing the existing files to be analyzed.
:EHELP.
